 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 10 — Human-in-the-Loop\n",
    "\n",
    "**Model:** DeepSeek-V3 via Nebius AI Studio  \n",
    "**Pattern:** Checkpointed Graph with Approval Gates  \n",
    "**Difficulty:** ⭐⭐⭐☆☆\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## The Problem\n",
    "\n",
    "Fully autonomous agents are powerful — and risky. An agent that can send emails, modify databases, or call external APIs can cause real damage if it makes a wrong decision.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Human-in-the-Loop (HITL)** adds approval gates at critical decision points. The agent pauses, presents its intended action to a human, and only proceeds if approved. The human can also provide corrections, which the agent incorporates before retrying.\n",
    "\n",
    "LangGraph's `interrupt` mechanism is designed exactly for this: it pauses graph execution at a specified node, persists the state (so the graph can resume later — even hours later), and waits for external input.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Architecture\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "START\n",
    "  │\n",
    "  ▼\n",
    "[Plan Action]         ← Agent decides what to do\n",
    "  │\n",
    "  ▼\n",
    "[⏸️ INTERRUPT]        ← Human reviews the plan\n",
    "  │                     (graph paused, state saved)\n",
    "  ├── Approved ──▶ [Execute Action] ──▶ END\n",
    "  │\n",
    "  └── Rejected  ──▶ [Revise Plan] ──▶ [⏸️ INTERRUPT again]\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "from dotenv import load_dotenv\n",
    "load_dotenv()\n",
    "\n",
    "from langchain_nebius import ChatNebius\n",
    "from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, SystemMessage, AIMessage\n",
    "from langgraph.graph import StateGraph, END\n",
    "from langgraph.checkpoint.memory import MemorySaver  # In-memory checkpointer\n",
    "from langgraph.types import interrupt, Command\n",
    "from typing import TypedDict, Optional, List\n",
    "\n",
    "llm = ChatNebius(\n",
    "    model=\"deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-V3\",\n",
    "    temperature=0,\n",
    "    api_key=os.environ[\"NEBIUS_API_KEY\"]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# MemorySaver persists state in-process.\n",
    "# For production, use SqliteSaver or PostgresSaver for durable cross-process persistence.\n",
    "checkpointer = MemorySaver()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Setup complete.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Scenario: Automated Email Draft Approval\n",
    "\n",
    "The agent drafts an email on the user's behalf. Before sending, it pauses for human review. The human can approve, reject with feedback, or edit the draft directly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class EmailState(TypedDict):\n",
    "    task: str               # What email to draft\n",
    "    draft: str              # Current draft\n",
    "    human_feedback: str     # What the human said during review\n",
    "    revision_count: int\n",
    "    approved: bool\n",
    "    sent: bool\n",
    "    action_log: List[str]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Nodes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def draft_email_node(state: EmailState) -> dict:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Draft an email based on the task description.\"\"\"\n",
    "    is_revision = state[\"revision_count\"] > 0\n",
    "    context = f\"Previous draft:\\n{state['draft']}\\n\\nHuman feedback: {state['human_feedback']}\" if is_revision else \"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    action = \"Revising\" if is_revision else \"Drafting\"\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n[Agent] {action} email...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    response = llm.invoke([\n",
    "        SystemMessage(content=(\n",
    "            \"You are a professional email writer. \"\n",
    "            \"Write clear, concise, professional emails. \"\n",
    "            \"Always include Subject, To (placeholder), and Body.\"\n",
    "        )),\n",
    "        HumanMessage(content=(\n",
    "            f\"Task: {state['task']}\\n\\n{context}\\n\\n\"\n",
    "            f\"{'Revise the email addressing the feedback above.' if is_revision else 'Write the email.'}\"\n",
    "        ))\n",
    "    ])\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f\"[Agent] Draft ready ({len(response.content)} chars).\")\n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        \"draft\": response.content,\n",
    "        \"revision_count\": state[\"revision_count\"] + (1 if is_revision else 0),\n",
    "        \"action_log\": state[\"action_log\"] + [f\"Draft {'revised' if is_revision else 'created'} (revision #{state['revision_count']})\"],\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def human_review_node(state: EmailState) -> dict:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    INTERRUPT: Pause execution and present the draft to the human.\n",
    "    The graph will not continue until .invoke() or .update_state() is called\n",
    "    with human input.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n",
    "    print(\"🛑 HUMAN REVIEW REQUIRED\")\n",
    "    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n",
    "    print(state[\"draft\"])\n",
    "    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # This pauses the graph and waits for a human response.\n",
    "    # The response is injected via graph.invoke() with Command(resume=...)\n",
    "    human_response = interrupt({\n",
    "        \"message\": \"Review the email draft above. Options:\",\n",
    "        \"options\": {\n",
    "            \"approve\": \"Send the email as-is\",\n",
    "            \"<feedback>\": \"Provide feedback for revision\",\n",
    "            \"cancel\": \"Cancel the email entirely\"\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "    # human_response is whatever the human passes in via Command(resume=...)\n",
    "    decision = human_response.strip().lower()\n",
    "\n",
    "    if decision == \"approve\":\n",
    "        print(\"\\n[Human] ✅ Approved.\")\n",
    "        return {\"approved\": True, \"human_feedback\": \"\"}\n",
    "    elif decision == \"cancel\":\n",
    "        print(\"\\n[Human] ❌ Cancelled.\")\n",
    "        return {\"approved\": False, \"human_feedback\": \"cancelled\"}\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(f\"\\n[Human] ✏️ Revision requested: {decision}\")\n",
    "        return {\"approved\": False, \"human_feedback\": human_response}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def send_email_node(state: EmailState) -> dict:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Simulate sending the approved email.\"\"\"\n",
    "    print(\"\\n[Agent] 📧 Sending email...\")\n",
    "    # In production: call your email API (SendGrid, SES, Gmail API, etc.)\n",
    "    print(\"[Agent] Email sent successfully! (simulated)\")\n",
    "    return {\"sent\": True, \"action_log\": state[\"action_log\"] + [\"Email sent\"]}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def route_after_review(state: EmailState) -> str:\n",
    "    if state.get(\"human_feedback\") == \"cancelled\":\n",
    "        print(\"[Router] Email cancelled — ending.\")\n",
    "        return \"end\"\n",
    "    if state.get(\"approved\"):\n",
    "        return \"send\"\n",
    "    return \"revise\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Build the Graph\n",
    "\n",
    "Note: `interrupt_before` and `interrupt_after` are one way to add checkpoints. Here we use `interrupt()` inline inside the node for more control."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "builder = StateGraph(EmailState)\n",
    "builder.add_node(\"draft\", draft_email_node)\n",
    "builder.add_node(\"review\", human_review_node)\n",
    "builder.add_node(\"send\", send_email_node)\n",
    "\n",
    "builder.set_entry_point(\"draft\")\n",
    "builder.add_edge(\"draft\", \"review\")\n",
    "builder.add_conditional_edges(\n",
    "    \"review\",\n",
    "    route_after_review,\n",
    "    {\"send\": \"send\", \"revise\": \"draft\", \"end\": END}\n",
    ")\n",
    "builder.add_edge(\"send\", END)\n",
    "\n",
    "# IMPORTANT: checkpointer is required for interrupt() to work\n",
    "graph = builder.compile(checkpointer=checkpointer)\n",
    "print(\"Human-in-the-Loop graph compiled.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Live Demo\n",
    "\n",
    "Each `graph.invoke()` call with the same `thread_id` continues from where it left off."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Thread ID uniquely identifies this conversation/session\n",
    "config = {\"configurable\": {\"thread_id\": \"email-demo-01\"}}\n",
    "\n",
    "initial_state = {\n",
    "    \"task\": (\n",
    "        \"Write a follow-up email to a potential client (Ahmed at TechCorp) \"\n",
    "        \"after a product demo yesterday. We showed our AI analytics platform. \"\n",
    "        \"Mention the 14-day free trial offer and offer to answer questions.\"\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    \"draft\": \"\",\n",
    "    \"human_feedback\": \"\",\n",
    "    \"revision_count\": 0,\n",
    "    \"approved\": False,\n",
    "    \"sent\": False,\n",
    "    \"action_log\": []\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# First run: agent drafts the email, then interrupts for review\n",
    "print(\"Starting agent...\")\n",
    "result = graph.invoke(initial_state, config=config)\n",
    "print(\"\\nGraph paused — awaiting human input.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# HUMAN DECISION: Request a revision\n",
    "# In a real app, this input comes from a UI, Slack bot, email, etc.\n",
    "print(\"Simulating human feedback: requesting revision...\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "result = graph.invoke(\n",
    "    Command(resume=\"Make it shorter — max 3 sentences in the body. And add a specific call-to-action for scheduling a call.\"),\n",
    "    config=config\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(\"\\nGraph paused again — awaiting approval of revised draft.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# HUMAN DECISION: Approve\n",
    "print(\"Simulating human approval...\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "result = graph.invoke(Command(resume=\"approve\"), config=config)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(\"ACTION LOG\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "for entry in result[\"action_log\"]:\n",
    "    print(f\"  • {entry}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Key Takeaways\n",
    "\n",
    "| Concept | Implementation |\n",
    "|---------|---------------|\n",
    "| **`interrupt()`** | Pauses graph mid-node; state is serialized and saved |\n",
    "| **`Command(resume=...)`** | Resumes a paused graph with human input |\n",
    "| **Thread ID** | Same thread = same conversation; different thread = new session |\n",
    "| **MemorySaver** | In-process only; swap for `SqliteSaver` in production |\n",
    "\n",
    "## What's Next\n",
    "\n",
    "**Notebook 11** scales from one to many: a 3-tier **Hierarchical Agent** system where strategic, tactical, and execution layers each have distinct responsibilities."
   ]
  }
